{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2dd736d2-5403-4512-a928-18f5b7f15aa8","content":"On macOS, the OS automatically generates **`.ips` crash reports** when a process crashes. You don't need `createdump`.\n\n**Where to find them:**\n\n1. **`~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/`** — user-level crashes\n2. **`/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/`** — system-level crashes\n\nLook for a file named like `YourAppName-YYYY-MM-DD-HHMMSS.ips`.\n\n**Quick lookup:**\n```bash\nls -lt ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/*.ips | head\n```\n\nYou can also open **Console.app → Crash Reports** to browse them with a GUI.\n\n**For a core dump** (if you need one for `lldb`):\n```bash\nulimit -c unlimited\n```\nSet this *before* running your app. Core files land in `/cores/`.\n\nIf you need to symbolicate the `.ips` crash log against .NET runtime symbols, let me know — I can help with that too.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"edb16f6a-ac50-47c5-be3c-35f7a80ac287","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT app on macOS when `createdump` isn't available. This is a knowledge question - I don't need to search code or run commands. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":321,"requestId":"1B81:5CDBF:E0CC6E:10038BB:6A0286DF"},"id":"e0a3286e-009e-4420-8904-19214ba9fd5a","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:48:26.736Z","parentId":"ad4787ea-d3d4-4897-a983-6cb9a7839569"}
